<td tEditID="c1r1" style=" background-color:#FFFFFF; color:#000000; bEditID:r3st1; bLabel:main; font-size:12pt; font-family:arial;" aEditID="c1r1" locked="0" >
<![CDATA[<div style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: arial; font-size: 12pt; text-align: right;"><span class="Apple-style-span" style="font-family: 'Times New Roman', Times, serif; "><font class="Apple-style-span" color="#000066" size="6">{!Contact.SchoolText__c}</font></span></div><div style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: arial; font-size: 12pt; text-align: right;"><font class="Apple-style-span" face="'Times New Roman', Times, serif" color="#ff6600" size="4"><i>Chartered By The British Schools Foundation</i></font></div><div style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: arial; font-size: 12pt; text-align: right;"><font class="Apple-style-span" face="Arial, sans-serif" color="#c0c0c0" size="6"><b><i><br></i></b></font></div><div style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: arial; font-size: 12pt; text-align: right;"><font style="background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);" face="Arial, sans-serif"><br></font></div><div style="text-align: left;"><div><font class="Apple-style-span" face="Arial, sans-serif" style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: arial; font-size: 12pt;"><span class="Apple-style-span" style="border-spacing: 5px;">Dear&nbsp;{!Contact.Salutation} {!Contact.LastName},<br><br></span></font><p><font face="arial">The health and safety of your children is our top priority. In addition to taking all necessary&nbsp;</font><span style="font-size: 12pt;">precautions, we aim to always keep our parents well informed of anything which comes to our&nbsp;</span><span style="font-size: 12pt;">attention which may affect your children.&nbsp;</span></p><p><font face="arial">I am writing to inform you that there has been a confirmed case of hand, foot and mouth&nbsp;</font><span style="font-size: 12pt;">disease in a pupil in one of our nursery classes. Hand, foot and mouth disease is a&nbsp;</span><span style="font-size: 12pt;">contagious, viral infection which spreads if contaminated droplets or bodily fluids are&nbsp;</span><span style="font-size: 12pt;">transferred from an infected person.&nbsp;</span><span style="font-size: 12pt;">Symptoms include cold-like symptoms such as:&nbsp;</span><span style="font-size: 12pt;">loss of&nbsp;</span><span style="font-size: 12pt;">appetite, headache, fatigue, irritability, cough, a moderately high temperature, a non-itchy red&nbsp;</span><span style="font-size: 12pt;">rash and painful mouth ulcers. Hand-foot-and-mouth disease may cause all of the above&nbsp;</span><span style="font-size: 12pt;">signs and symptoms or just a few of them. Please seek immediate medical advice and advise&nbsp;</span><span style="font-size: 12pt;">the school promptly if your child is unwell with any of the above symptoms.</span></p><p><font face="arial">At school, we are taking all precautions necessary including:&nbsp;</font></p><ul><li><span style="font-size: 12pt;">Ensuring all classrooms are disinfected with both ultra-violet light and a disinfectant</span></li><li><span style="font-size: 12pt;">Good ventilation of classrooms and other rooms</span></li><li><span style="font-size: 12pt;">Daily cleaning and disinfection of the door handles, stair railings, toys, bathroom&nbsp;</span><span style="font-size: 12pt;">accessories and food utensils</span></li><li><span style="font-size: 12pt;">Early Yearsâ€™ toys thoroughly disinfected every Friday</span></li><li><span style="font-size: 12pt;">Unwell children will see nurse and if necessary parents will be contacted</span></li><li><span style="font-size: 12pt;">The children have been taught how to wash their hands by teachers<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre">	</span></span></li></ul><font face="arial" style="font-size: 12pt;">If you believe your child has hand, foot and mouth disease, please</font><font face="arial" style="font-size: 12pt;">&nbsp;seek medical treatment,&nbsp;</font><span style="font-size: 12pt;">follow safety procedures at home and keep them away from school until they have recovered&nbsp;</span><span style="font-size: 12pt;">from the illness.&nbsp;</span><p><font face="arial">For further information about hand, foot and mouth disease, please <a href="http://www.nhs.uk/conditions/Hand-foot-and-mouth-disease/Pages/Introduction.aspx">follow this link.</a></font></p><div><br></div></div><span lang="en-GB" style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: arial; font-size: 12pt;"><div style="margin: 0px;"><font face="Arial,Sans-Serif" color="#000000" size="3"><div style="margin: 0px;"><div style="margin: 0px;">Warm Regards,<br></div>Alison Mackey</div><div style="margin: 0px;">Deputy Head of Primary</div></font></div></span></div><div style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: arial; font-size: 12pt; text-align: left;"><font class="Apple-style-span" face="Arial, sans-serif"><span class="Apple-style-span" style="border-spacing: 5px;"><div><p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align: justify; "><br></p></div></span></font></div><div style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: arial; font-size: 12pt; text-align: left;"><font class="Apple-style-span" face="Arial, sans-serif">{!Contact.SchoolText__c}</font></div><div style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: arial; font-size: 12pt; text-align: left;"><span class="Apple-style-span" style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif; "><i><font class="Apple-style-span" color="#ff6600"><b>World Class Education</b></font></i></span></div><div style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: arial; font-size: 12pt; text-align: left;"><font class="Apple-style-span" face="Arial, sans-serif"><br></font></div><div style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: arial; font-size: 12pt; text-align: left;"><font class="Apple-style-span" face="Arial, sans-serif">__________________________________________________________</font></div><div style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: arial; font-size: 12pt; text-align: center;"><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="1">{!User.School_List_Email_Footer__c}</font><font class="Apple-style-span" style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: arial; font-size: 12pt;" face="Arial, sans-serif" 